 and soft drinks from the definition of eligible foods under 7 C.F.R. 271.2. If such waiver is granted, then the Secretary shall prohibit the purchase of candy and soft drinks with benefits provided through the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program. If no such waiver is granted, then the cabinet Secretary shall request such a waiver annually until such waiver is granted. NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to enhance nutrition in the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: